# Confirm modals (no native dialogs)

Destructive or irreversible actions must ask for confirmation through an **in-app modal** — never the browser’s native `confirm()` / `alert()` and never HTMX `hx-confirm`.

## Forbidden

- `hx-confirm="…"` on any element
- `window.confirm()`, `window.alert()`, `window.prompt()`
- Selenium `driver.switchTo().alert()` in new tests (use the confirm modal DSL instead)

Legacy templates may still use `hx-confirm` or `onclick` modal close; do not extend that pattern — migrate when touching the file.

## Required pattern

1. **Trigger** opens a server-rendered modal into `#modal-container`:

```html
<button type="button"
        hx-get="/components/confirm-modal/post-unpublish/{post.id}"
        hx-target="#modal-container"
        hx-swap="innerHTML">
```

2. **Modal** lives in [`ConfirmModalEndpoint`](../../src/main/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/components/ConfirmModalEndpoint.java) + [`confirmModal.html`](../../src/main/resources/templates/ConfirmModalEndpoint/confirmModal.html). It shows title, message, **Cancel**, and a confirm control with `data-confirm-submit` that carries the real `hx-post` / `hx-delete`.

3. **Target element** for the mutation must be addressable globally (e.g. `data-post-id` on the row + `hx-target="[data-post-id='{id}']"`), because the modal is outside `#main`.

4. **Chrome** — close via `[data-confirm-modal-close]`, Escape, or auto-close after successful confirm (`confirm-modal.js`). Use existing `.modal`, `.modal--open`, `.modal__container` blocks ([ui-elements.md](../../docs/ui-elements.md)).

## Adding a new confirm variant

1. Add a case to `ConfirmModalAction` with i18n keys (title, message, confirm label) aligned with [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md).
2. Add `@GET @Path("…")` on `ConfirmModalEndpoint` that authorizes the action and renders `ConfirmModalView`.
3. Wire the trigger button with `hx-get` — no inline confirmation copy on the trigger.

## Tests

Extend `App` to click the trigger, then `#confirmModal [data-confirm-submit]` — never `alert().accept()`.

See also [contraponto-javascript.mdc](contraponto-javascript.mdc) and [docs/htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md).
